00:09:50,140 --> 00:09:52,780
{\an8}黑色安息日

125
00:09:51,260 --> 00:09:53,860
我們中有巫師  塞勒姆有惡魔
Witches among us, the devil in Salem.

126
00:09:54,730 --> 00:09:55,540
給您  先生
For you, sir.

127
00:09:57,850 --> 00:09:58,650
給您  先生
For you, sir.

128
00:09:59,050 --> 00:09:59,850
不用
No.

129
00:10:05,790 --> 00:10:06,460
{\an8}{\pos(185.231,166.091)}塞勒姆教堂
上帝賜予我們力量

130
00:10:15,820 --> 00:10:16,960
慢點  慢點
Easy. Easy.

131
00:11:01,260 --> 00:11:03,150
這里是奧登家
This is the Alden house,

132
00:11:03,620 --> 00:11:06,030
奧登家的人已經都死光了
and there ain't any Aldens left.

133
00:11:06,380 --> 00:11:11,170
所以你要么是鬼魂  要么就要成為鬼魂了
So you are either a ghost, or you're about to be one.

134
00:11:11,170 --> 00:11:13,470
這樣歡迎別人回家可不是待客之道啊
That's a harsh way to say "Welcome home."

135
00:11:15,150 --> 00:11:16,090
約翰
Johnny?

136
00:11:16,500 --> 00:11:17,540
怎么可能
Can't be.

137
00:11:17,970 --> 00:11:21,130
我聽說你死了啊  戰死了
I heard you was dead -- killed in the war.

138
00:11:21,130 --> 00:11:23,100
我倒是希望死了
I wished I was a couple of times.

139
00:11:23,100 --> 00:11:25,940
好人是不會輕易就死了的
Ah, well, they can't keep a good man down.

140
00:11:32,850 --> 00:11:35,300
我在來的路上看到三個人被絞死示眾
Saw three men strung up on the way into town

141
00:11:35,300 --> 00:11:37,580
公共集會地中間還建了一個新絞刑架
and a new gallows being built in the heart of the common.

142
00:11:37,580 --> 00:11:38,810
這是怎么回事
What the hell is that?

143
00:11:38,820 --> 00:11:43,890
我們的塞勒姆因為巫師的事人心惶惶
Precious Salem caught up in a stinking witch panic.

144
00:11:43,890 --> 00:11:44,980
巫師
Witch panic?

145
00:11:45,630 --> 00:11:48,650
有權有勢的那些人又派誰去平息了
Who did the bigwigs send in to put out the fire,

146
00:11:48,650 --> 00:11:50,470
那個對上帝深信不疑的麥哲嗎
the Almighty increase Mather?

147
00:11:50,470 --> 00:11:54,210
不  是他兒子柯頓
No, his son -- Cotton.

148
00:11:54,220 --> 00:11:57,460
只可惜他比起父親差遠了  就是個廢物
And not a chip off the old block -- barely a splinter.

149
00:11:57,460 --> 00:11:58,890
我記得我們小時候
I remember when we were kids

150
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:01,190
他就穿得跟個姑娘似的
he used to dress like a girl.

151
00:12:01,410 --> 00:12:02,460
打起架來也扭扭捏捏
Fought like one, too.

152
00:12:02,460 --> 00:12:04,620
他現在長大了
Well, he's all growed-up now.

153
00:12:04,630 --> 00:12:07,130
長成了滿身纏著綾羅綢緞的傻子
A fine fool in fine silk clothes,

154
00:12:07,130 --> 00:12:09,560
但不是普通的傻子  而是最危險的那種
and not just any fool, the most dangerous kind --

155
00:12:09,560 --> 00:12:11,570
自以為無所不知
the kind that thinks he knows everything.

156
00:12:12,080 --> 00:12:15,260
你回來不是為了聽這些屁話的吧
But you didn't come back for all this horseshit.

157
00:12:15,260 --> 00:12:19,960
你回來的目的只有一個
You come back for one thing and one thing only.

158
00:12:19,960 --> 00:12:23,320
說實話  她現在過得很好
Truth told, she's finer than ever.

159
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:26,090
她是塞勒姆最富有的女人
And she's the richest woman in Salem.

160
00:12:26,820 --> 00:12:27,900
為什么呢
And why not?

161
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:30,660
因為她現在是西布里的妻子
She's mary Sibley now.

162
00:12:31,220 --> 00:12:32,470
{\pos(222.154,201.273)}西布里宅

163
00:12:49,710 --> 00:12:50,590
西布里
Sibley?

164
00:12:52,520 --> 00:12:53,730
喬治·西布里
George Sibley.

165
00:12:54,470 --> 00:12:55,050
但他妻子...
But his wife --

166
00:12:55,050 --> 00:12:56,700
幾年前去世了
Died a few years ago.

167
00:12:58,710 --> 00:13:00,990
你離開太長時間了  約翰
You've been gone a long time, John.

168
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:08,220
時刻做好準備吧
Keep your powder in your bag.

169
00:13:09,200 --> 00:13:10,170
有一天
One day,

170
00:13:10,460 --> 00:13:14,230
你的瑪麗會成為我們國家最富有的寡婦
your Mary will be the richest widow in the country.

171
00:13:22,360 --> 00:13:23,100
司機來了
The driver's at the door

172
00:13:23,100 --> 00:13:24,680
帶來了您的包裹  夫人
with some packages for you, ma'am.

173
00:13:25,220 --> 00:13:25,980
讓他進來
Send him in.

174
00:13:27,110 --> 00:13:30,070
納撒尼爾  帶西布里先生一起走吧
And, Nathaniel, take Mr. Sibley with you.

175
00:13:30,390 --> 00:13:31,640
到洗澡時間了
Time for his bath.

176
00:13:44,380 --> 00:13:47,910
艾薩克  現在告訴我都有哪些新聞吧
Now, Isaac, tell me some news of the world.

177
00:13:47,910 --> 00:13:50,720
今天看到一個人風塵仆仆地進城了
Saw a dusty fella walking into town today.

178
00:13:51,170 --> 00:13:52,880
我簡直不敢相信自己的眼睛
I couldn't believe my eyes.

179
00:13:53,470 --> 00:13:54,160
為什么
Why?

180
00:13:54,780 --> 00:13:55,900
那個人是約翰·奧登
It was John Alden.

181
00:14:14,390 --> 00:14:16,120
歡迎回來  麥哲牧師
Welcome back, Reverend Mather.

182
00:14:16,120 --> 00:14:18,090
朗姆酒   杜松子酒和麥芽酒
Rum, gin, ale?

183
